Perform PCR reaction by placing plate on thermal cycler and running program ML_Cleanup_PCR
After ML_Cleanup_PCR program completes, store the reaction plate at -20 °C or proceed directly to Step 4, Library pooling
Remove reaction plate either from thermal cycler or -20 °C storage. If plate is frozen, allow it to thaw completely (at least 15 min) at room temperature
Spin down the reaction plate and remove seal
Pool reactions by transferring an equal volume of each reaction into a single microcentrifuge tube. A minimum of 5 ul per reaction is recommended, and the total pool volume should be at least 100 ul
Proceed directly to next step, Library purification. Otherwise, place tube at -20 °C

Perform library purification using Kapa Pure Beads (or the equivalent) on 100 ul of pooled library, with a 0.8X bead ratio (80 ul beads), and elute in 10 ul 1X TE for a 10-fold concentration of the library
The purified library is ready for quantitation, dilution, and sequencing according to the sequencer manufacturer’s instructions, but should be stored at -20 °C until use
Load the purified pool into at least 3 wells, and load individual unpurified reactions, including the no-RNA control if used, into the remaining wells
Run the DNA 1000 program
